# Placeholder so the empty MacOS/ directory is tracked in git.
#
# At build / install time the cua-driver release binary (universal
# macOS slice — arm64 + x86_64 lipo'd together) is copied into this
# directory as `cua-driver`. The Info.plist's CFBundleExecutable
# points at that name.
#
# See:
#   - libs/cua-driver-rs/scripts/install.sh   (downloads the binary
#     from GitHub Releases, copies it into Contents/MacOS, installs
#     the bundle to /Applications/CuaDriverRs.app, and creates the
#     ~/.local/bin/cua-driver symlink pointing into the bundle)
#   - .github/workflows/cd-rust-cua-driver.yml  (bakes the assembled
#     .app into the darwin release tarball at CD time)
